# Decision log

Time-ordered log of decisions per cycle. Used to trace why a hypothesis was dropped or
why a particular method was chosen, after the fact.

## Format

```markdown
## YYYY-MM-DD cycle <N> (exp_<NNN>_<slug>)

- **Tested hypothesis**: H<id> (one-line restatement)
- **Observation**: [observed values, anomalies]
- **Verdict**: [supported / rejected / partial / parked]
- **Derived hypotheses**:
  - H<new> (run-now): ...
  - H<new> (next-session): ...
- **Direction rejected**: [what was tried and did not work, with reason]
- **Robustness battery status**: [which items in robustness_battery.md passed / failed]
```

## Example

```markdown
## YYYY-MM-DD cycle 5 (exp_005_signal_flip)

- **Tested hypothesis**: H3 (entry filter × signal-flip exit beats fee 0.5 bp/side)
- **Observation**:
  - val Sharpe +0.52 (fee 1 bp), +1.45 (fee 0)
  - win 62.4% (val) / 62.3% (test) — preserved across the split
  - Walk-forward mean Sharpe -0.10, pct_positive 47.4% (unstable)
  - Bootstrap 95% CI = [0.009, 0.202], p=0.014 — significant but small effect size
- **Verdict**: partial (negative at fee 1 bp, borderline at 0.5 bp, walk-forward unstable)
- **Derived hypotheses**:
  - H10 (run-now): vol-targeted size to stabilize walk-forward
  - H11 (next-session): multi-asset generalization
  - H12 (run-now): regime-conditional Sharpe (trending vs. ranging)
- **Direction rejected**: time-stop alone as exit (effect size < fee). Reason: signal
  horizon and exit horizon do not coincide.
- **Robustness battery**: 4 of 7 passed (threshold ✓ / fee ✓ / bootstrap CI border /
  walk-forward ✗ / DSR not computed / realistic cost not run / regime not run)
```

## Notes

- Do not delete. Negative results stay.
- Use specific numbers ("Sharpe -1.74" rather than "Sharpe was low")
- Always classify derived hypotheses (run-now / next-session / drop)
